&quot;Chaining or nesting a series of function calls, depending on the language, can be more readable still than the variables approach and at the same time more concise&quot;.<p>Couldnt agree more, variables are just clutter you have to keep mental track of, and working with series of transformations is much easier (for me at least) to process. I would be interested to know if its like this for all developers, perhaps not, since I know some that are also opposed to recursion.<p>but for me this:<p><pre><code>    sum([]) = 0.
    sum([H|T]) = H + sum(T).
</code></pre>
is much easier to understand than:<p><pre><code>    function sum(ary) {
      var i = ary.length,
       res;
      while(--i) {
        res += ary[i];
      }
      return res;
    }</code></pre>
